reviews.text:
Couldn’t find the entrance to a coffee shop which is located inside an industrial building, as the main gate was closed on Sunday, so I picked another random coffee shop before heading to a yoga class.

This Irish Cream Latte is not a real Irish coffee. There is no cream or alcohol, only Irish cream syrup, which is quite sweet indeed. Well, at least it’s smooth. It actually made me crave for an authentic Irish coffee! I wonder where can I get one other than the one I had in Peng Chau…
It's alright, the coffee is good, not an ideal for a chilling out.
Tucked away from busy APM mall. A gem in the streets of Kwun Tong. Excellent coffee and their tiramisu is to die for. A cosy decor filled with elements of nature.

A small, cosy coffee shop with shared seating. 

Nice selection of coffee, tea and food at reasonable prices.
Love their caramel latte, smooth but not milky. The cafe is nice for a short stay rather than a place to read or work with computer.

reviews.text: A small veggie cafe. Love the veggie food here. Burger, salad are personal favorite. No choice over daily soup but so far all are fine to me. Organic Soya milk or Pukka tea come with the set meal . No coffee available . May be kitchen not big enough to offer too many options.
Good idea to use veggie only to do spaghetti carbonara , taste ok but it's not similar at all

Good little place in a food court. Burger was nice (though a tad small), staff was friendly. I would go again, but you've gotta be in the neighborhood, which is not exactly the center of the universe.
Just the best veggie food 😘
Completely vegan and delicious! For $97 I had a beverage, salad, soup and entree. Yummy yummy. It's a small spot inside a food arcade, must try!
